    "The League table contains a unique ID for each league, along with the country ID and the name of the league.",
    "This table can be used to identify different football leagues and their associated countries.",
    "### Country ('Country') This table simply maps each country's unique ID to its name, allowing for easy identification of countries in the dataset.",
    "### Player Attributes ('Player_Attributes') Similar to the Team Attributes table but for individual players, this table includes detailed ratings and scores for various skills and attributes (e.g., crossing, finishing, dribbling, defensive skills) as well as the player's preferred foot, attacking and defensive work rates.",
    "These attributes are rated numerically, typically on a scale from 0 to 100, providing a quantitative measure of a player's abilities and potential."
